Recently, I had the opportunity to identify a vulnerability in the Endpoint Privilege Manager (EPM) module of CyberArk. This discovery involves a bypass in software controls using the Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL), which could impact the security of systems relying on this tool.
In my article, I share details about the vulnerability, its potential impact, and possible mitigation measures to help safeguard corporate environments.

